gw.api.domain.delinquency

Interface DelinquencyTarget

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Account, PolicyPeriod

    public interface DelinquencyTarget
    An entity that can be made delinquent should implement this interface

      • getDelinquencyProcesses

        DelinquencyProcess[] getDelinquencyProcesses()
        Gets all the deliquency processes on the target, if any exist. Aggregate entities will return their children's delinquency processes as well as their own. Returns empty array otherwise.
        Returns:
        an array of DelinquencyProcesses

      • getActiveDelinquencyProcesses

        java.util.List<? extends DelinquencyProcess> getActiveDelinquencyProcesses(DelinquencyReason reason)
        Gets the active delinquency processes on the target for a given delinquency reason, if any exist. Aggregate entities will return their children's delinquency processes as well as their own. Returns empty List otherwise.
        Parameters:
        reason - the reason given when starting the delinquency.
        Returns:
        the matching delinquency process.

      • getActiveDelinquencyProcesses

        java.util.List<? extends DelinquencyProcess> getActiveDelinquencyProcesses()
        Gets the active delinquency processes on the target, for all reasons, if any exist. Aggregate entities will return their children's delinquency processes as well as their own. Returns an empty List otherwise.
        Returns:
        a List of all delinquency processes on the target.

      • getEarliestActiveDelinquencyProcess

        DelinquencyProcess getEarliestActiveDelinquencyProcess()
        Gets the active delinquency process on the target, for all reasons, that started the earliest. Aggregate entities will return a child's delinquency process if it started before one of its own. Returns null otherwise.
        Returns:
        the earliest delinquency process on the target.

      • hasActiveDelinquencyProcess

        boolean hasActiveDelinquencyProcess()
        Returns:
        true if there is at least one active delinquency process on the target.

      • isDelinquent

        boolean isDelinquent()
        Returns true if the due amount for the target is positive. Aggregate entities will return the sum of their children's delinquency processes as well as their own

        Note that this doesn't base its return value on the existence of an active delinquency process on the target. To do that, use hasActiveDelinquencyProcess().

        Returns:
        true if the due amount for the target is positive

      • isEligibleToStartDelinquency

        boolean isEligibleToStartDelinquency()
        Returns true if the delinquent amount exceeds the DelinquencyPlan's "enter delinquency" threshold, and if the plugin method IEventHandler.canStartDelinquencyProcess(DelinquencyTarget) returns true. Note: Does NOT consider holds or the existence of a delinquency process targeting this policy.
        Returns:
        true if the target can enter delinquency according to the DelinquencyPlan

      • startDelinquency

        DelinquencyProcess startDelinquency(DelinquencyReason reason)
        Creates a DelinquencyProcess instance for the target and starts its processing, including event setup, workflow, etc. It does not do any checking such as whether this target already has an active delinqueny process. The caller is responsible for making the necessary checks. Does not create instances or start deliquency processes for any children entities.
        Parameters:
        reason - the reason the delinquency is being started
        Returns:
        the delinquency process that was created

      • getDisplayName

        java.lang.String getDisplayName()
        Returns:
        The display name for the target entity
